        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 11 at 5:50PM CDT by NWS Lubbock TX</headline>
        <description>At 550 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Littlefield, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Littlefield, Amherst, and Fieldton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, seek shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
